<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 27 at 3:14AM EST  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...AREAS OF FOG DEVELOPING, DENSE FOG POSSIBLE...
Areas of fog will continue to develop over portions of Effingham
and Chatham Counties in Southeast Georgia through 5 AM. The fog
will be locally dense at times with visibilities 1/4 mile or less
at times. More widespread dense fog could form after 5 AM and a
Dense Fog Advisory may be needed, possibly including the Savannah
Metro Area.</description>
<instruction>If driving, slow down and leave extra distance ahead of you in
case a sudden stop is needed.</instruction>
